The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 London, July 26: Moodys Investors Service today upgraded the rating of Tata Motors Ltd, reflecting the company?s dominant position in the commercial vehicle sector. Moodys upgraded the company?s senior unsecured rating from Ba2 to Ba1. The rating agency has also assigned a Ba1 corporate family rating (previously known as senior implied rating) to Tata Motors. The outlook for the ratings is stable. 

 New Delhi, July 26: The tax authorities today issued guidelines for registration of stock exchanges for trading in derivatives. A notification issued by the Central Board of Direct Taxes (CBDT) said registration of bourses is necessary to ensure that the board recognises such trading as non-speculative.

 New Delhi, July 26: The government is ascertaining whether the Airbus Industrie had offered aircraft to other airlines at a lower price than what was offered to Indian Airlines, the Rajya Sabha was informed today. 

 New Delhi, July 26: General Electric has set up a corporate growth team in India as part of efforts to increase its revenues to $3 billion by 2008 from $0.8 billion in 2004. 

 New Delhi, July 26: Tata Investment Corporation Ltd will issue bonus shares to shareholders in the ratio of one share for every two held.




